parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the entry step to extend can cause accidents, injuries, or difficulties when exiting the coach, especially in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The entry step does not always extend out when the door is opened
leaving a gap between the coach and the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Incorrect tire pressure certification can lead to premature tire failure, blowouts, or loss of control, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The certification label shows incorrect tire pressure information
which can cause the consumer to underinflate or overinflate the tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front wheel bearings can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents or loss of vehicle stability.
symptoms: Grease leaking from the front wheels
the vehicle pulls to one side (in this case
to the right)
the vehicle may vibrate or make noise while driving
the vehicle may have uneven tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Goodyear Tire Failure - Tread Separation/Tread Rivering
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of Goodyear tires due to tread separation or tread rivering can lead to sudden blowouts, loss of control, and accidents, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Tread separation
tread rivering
tire blowout
loss of tire pressure
vibration while driving
uneven tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents. In extreme temperatures, it can also lead to heat-related illnesses.
symptoms: The air conditioner is not blowing cold air
the air conditioner is not turning on
the air conditioner is making unusual noises
the air conditioner is leaking refrigerant.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the compartment heater can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents. In extreme cold temperatures, it can also lead to hypothermia.
symptoms: The compartment heater is not producing heat
the compartment heater is not turning on
the compartment heater is making unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the roof air ventilation system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The roof air vent is not functioning properly
the roof air vent is making unusual noises
the roof air vent is not opening or closing properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the side mirror control can cause reduced visibility, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The side mirror control is not functioning properly
the side mirror control is only half working
the side mirror is not adjusting properly.
